   <head>TO THE READER.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">T</seg>Hrough two fieldes, Christian Reader, the way is directed: the one full of Briers, hath the perfest Path to Saluation, the other (more pleasant to the vi<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>cious minde) leades to endlesse misorie: church with aduice, and shun with discretion. And to me thy vnknown frtend, lend (I pray thee) us friendly iudg<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ment, as I shall wish for thy prosporous estate: farewell.</p>
